<!--Tsuge Mikumari Shrine-->

'''Tsuge Mikumari Shrine''' (都祁水分神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinto shrine|qq=}} located in {{ill|Nara City|ja|奈良市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nara City|qq=}}, Nara Prefecture, Japan. It is classified as a {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|qq=}} (major shrine) and formerly held the Rank of a [[prefectural shrine]] under the old shrine Ranking system.
== Enshrined Deities == The shrine venerates the following three deities: * {{ill|Hayakitsuhiko and Hayakitsuhime|ja|ハヤアキツヒコ・ハヤアキツヒメ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hayakitsuhiko and Hayakitsuhime|qq=}} * {{ill|Mikumari|ja|水分神|fr|Mikumari|sv|Mikumari|lt=Ame-no-Mikumari-no-Kami|ja|天水分神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mikumari|qq=}} (Heavenly Water Distribution Deity) * {{ill|Mikumari|ja|水分神|fr|Mikumari|sv|Mikumari|lt=Kuni-no-Mikumari-no-Kami|ja|国水分神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mikumari|qq=}} (Earthly Water Distribution Deity)
== History ==
=== Early History === The exact founding date of the shrine is unknown, but it is traditionally believed to have been established during the {{ill|Asuka period|ja|飛鳥時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Asuka period|qq=}}. Initially located at the site of {{ill|Tsuge Yamaguchi Shrine|ja|都祁山口神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuge Yamaguchi Shrine|qq=}}, it was later moved to its current location, believed to have been used as the Horigoe Temporary Palace during the reign of Emperor Shōmu. The area served as a lodging site for the imperial princesses who were priestesses of the Ise Grand Shrine during the {{ill|Heian period|ja|平安時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Heian period|qq=}}.
The shrine was listed as a major shrine in the {{ill|Engishiki|ja|延喜式|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki|qq=}} and received offerings during the {{ill|Tsukinami-no-Matsuri|ja|月次祭|1=Tsukinami-no-Matsuri|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsukinami-no-Matsuri|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsukinami-no-Matsuri|qq=}} and {{ill|Niiname-no-Matsuri|ja|新嘗祭|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Niiname-no-Matsuri|qq=}}.
=== Medieval Period === During the medieval period, the shrine's lands became part of the estate of {{ill|Kōfuku-ji|ja|興福寺|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōfuku-ji|qq=}}, specifically under the Kita-in sub-temple of the Nikaidō lineage. As the estate developed, the worship of water deities grew in importance. In 972 (Tenroku 3), the shrine was relocated to its current site in Tomoda. The current main shrine building was constructed in 1499 (Meiō 8) during the Muromachi period.
=== Divine Ranks === * {{ill|Shōwa (era)|ja|承和|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōwa (era)|qq=}} 7 (840), October 7: Elevated from unranked to Junior Fifth Rank, Lower ({{ill|Shoku Nihongi|ja|続日本後紀|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shoku Nihongi|qq=}}) * {{ill|Tian’an|ja|天安|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tian’an|qq=}} 3 (859), January 27: Elevated from Junior Fifth Rank, Lower to Senior Fifth Rank, Lower ({{ill|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|ja|日本三代実録|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|qq=}})
